---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About | Creative License">
  <section class="about-page">
    <header class="about-hero">
        <h1 class="about-kicker">Creative License</p>
      <h1 class="intro">is a thesis project about rules as creative force.</h1>
      <p class="about-intro">
        The site treats constraint as a method, not a limitation. Each section documents a
        different relationship to rules, from the external structures that shape production to
        the internal habits that guide decision-making.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="about-grid">
      <article class="about-panel">
        <h2>What the project does</h2>
        <p>
          It brings together work, craft, and self-directed prompts as a single system. The
          videos, layouts, and rule sets are meant to feel connected, so the site reads as both an
          archive and an active process.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="about-panel">
        <h2>How to read it</h2>
        <p>
          Start with the main sections in the top navigation. Work shows outcomes, Craft focuses on
          process, and Self looks at the internal rules that shape making. The page structure is
          intentionally direct so the ideas can stay front and center.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="about-panel about-panel--wide">
        <h2>Core idea</h2>
        <p>
          Rules can narrow the field of possibility, but they also create momentum. By making the
          constraints visible, the project asks how decisions change when the boundaries are clear,
          and what kind of work appears when control is reduced.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    width: min(100%, var(--size-page-width));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2.5rem) var(--size-page-padding) 4rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .about-hero,
  .about-panel {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--radius-inner);
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  }

  .about-hero {
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .about-hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-headings);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 7vw, 5.5rem);
    line-height: 0.92;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    max-width: 15ch;
    font-weight: normal;
  }

    .about-kicker {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-background);
    font-family: var(--font-headings);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    background: white;
    font-variation-settings: "wdth" 150, "wght" 900, "slnt" 0;
    rotate: -2deg;
  }
  .about-intro,
  .about-panel p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.5vw, 1.15rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 70ch;
  }

  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .about-panel {
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-panel h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-headings);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .about-panel--wide {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }

  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .about-panel--wide {
      grid-column: auto;
    }
  }
</style>